---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { url } from '../lib/url';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="Abhi Yadav — 15+ years in identity & access management. San Francisco–based writer and speaker on the future of digital identity."
>
  <section class="section-tight">
    <div class="container about-head">
      <div class="about-portrait" aria-hidden="true">
        <img src={url('/images/headshot.svg')} alt="" width="200" height="200" />
      </div>
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
        <h1>Abhi Yadav</h1>
        <p class="lede">
          Identity &amp; access management practitioner, writer, and speaker —
          based in San Francisco.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container section-tight">
    <div class="prose about-body">
      <p>
        My interest in cybersecurity began as a teenager, just as the internet
        was emerging. A turning point came with the 1997 Mars Rover mission — I
        was captivated by technology’s power to unite people around a shared
        goal. I’ve been chasing that feeling ever since.
      </p>

      <p>
        Over the past 15+ years I’ve worked alongside many of the innovators in
        the identity and access management space. That journey has included an
        early startup focused on solving access-control challenges, a role at
        <strong>Sun Microsystems</strong> following its acquisition,
        collaborations with industry architects on solutions and standards, and
        work with product leaders shaping the vision for identity.
      </p>

      <h2>How I think about this work</h2>
      <p>
        I believe in the <strong>Feynman technique</strong>: the best way to
        learn something is to teach it. This blog is where I do that — working
        through ideas in public, in plain language. I keep the writing
        vendor-neutral except where an article is explicitly sponsored, and the
        opinions here are my own.
      </p>

      <blockquote>
        Views on this blog are mine and do not represent those of my employers.
      </blockquote>

      <h2>Community</h2>
      <p>I’m involved with organizations advancing digital identity, including:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Digital ID &amp; Authentication Council of Canada (DIACC)</li>
        <li>IDPro — the home for digital identity professionals</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Let’s talk</h2>
      <p>
        I’m always happy to compare notes with others working in identity. The
        best way to reach me is via the <a href={url('/contact')}>contact page</a>, or
        come see where I’m <a href={url('/speaking')}>speaking next</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about-head {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: clamp(1.25rem, 4vw, 2.5rem);
    max-width: var(--maxw-prose);
  }
  .about-portrait img {
    width: clamp(110px, 18vw, 180px);
    height: auto;
    aspect-ratio: 1;
    border-radius: 50%;
    object-fit: cover;
    border: 4px solid var(--paper);
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-lift);
    background: var(--accent-soft);
    flex: none;
  }
  .about-body { font-size: 1.08rem; }
  .about-body h2 { margin-top: 2.2rem; }
  @media (max-width: 560px) {
    .about-head { flex-direction: column; align-items: flex-start; }
  }
</style>
